title: Lyndon B Johnson National Historical Park: Amphibians
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Animals     Amphibians                Amphibians         Gray Tree Frog   Habitats for amphibians at Lyndon B. Johnson National Historical Park include the Pedernales River, Town Creek, multiple stock tanks, and natural springs and seeps. These areas support multiple varieties of amphibians. There is an abundance of frogs, toads and salamanders that take advantage of these moist habitats.
